# Deployment Rules

## CRITICAL: Always Test Production Build Locally

`npm run dev` !== `npm run build`. Dev mode hides minification bugs.

```bash
npm run build && npm start   # Run before EVERY deploy
```

| Aspect | Dev | Build |
|--------|-----|-------|
| Minification | None | SWC (can break libs) |
| Env vars | .env.local direct | May be processed/stripped |
| Errors | Hot reload recovers | Build fails hard |

## Vercel Environment Variables

- Supabase URL and keys are **base64-encoded** in Vercel env vars, decoded at runtime in `src/lib/supabase/env.ts`
- `NEXT_PUBLIC_*` vars: Do NOT mark as "Sensitive" — must be available at build time
- `SUPABASE_SERVICE_ROLE_KEY`: Keep as "Sensitive", server-only
- Set scope to "All Environments", remove trailing slashes from URLs
- When adding new Supabase env vars → always base64-encode on Vercel

### Why base64?

Vercel's build can strip `NEXT_PUBLIC_*` values from JS bundles. Base64 encoding makes them invisible to the build process.

### Verify after deploy:
```js
fetch('/_next/static/chunks/[chunk].js').then(r=>r.text()).then(t=>console.log(t.indexOf('your-url')))
// -1 means Vercel stripped it
```

## Supabase Auth — Cookie Rules

- Cookie name `"hlaiyxpiebmvkb-auth-token"` must match in server.ts, client.ts, and middleware
- Use `@supabase/ssr` (not `@supabase/supabase-js`) for cookie-based auth

## Supabase RLS

- RLS must be enabled on ALL public tables
- Add policies IMMEDIATELY when creating tables:
```sql
CREATE POLICY "auth_all_tablename" ON public.tablename
FOR ALL TO authenticated USING (true) WITH CHECK (true);
```
- Never use custom functions in policies unless verified they exist

## SheetJS — NEVER Import Directly

SWC minifier corrupts xlsx. Solution already implemented:

- ✅ `const XLSX = await loadXlsx()` — from `src/lib/loadXlsx.ts`
- ❌ NEVER: `import * as XLSX from "xlsx"` or `await import("xlsx")`
- xlsx npm package is for TypeScript types ONLY
- If upgrading xlsx, also update `public/xlsx.full.min.js`

## Files in /public That Must Exist

- `xlsx.full.min.js` — SheetJS pre-built (DO NOT DELETE)
- `favicon.ico` — generated by `node scripts/generate-pwa-icons.js`
- `icon-192.png`, `icon-512.png` — PWA icons
- `manifest.json` — PWA manifest
